A rare opportunity to secure a ground floor unit with office fitout and a storage area accessed via a roller door at the rear.

The premises also comprise a reception area, boardroom, kitchen and its own toilet facilites.

The unit comes with 2 designated car parks to the rear of the unit and plently of free customer / staff parking to the front.

The property is located in Phillip providing easy access to all areas of Canberra and only a short walk to Woden Shopping Centre and the bus interchange.

Call CBRE now to arrange an inspection.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Better Music is a wholly Australian owned music store successfully operating from two locations; 29-31 Colbee Court and 38 Botany Street, Phillip ACT. To better service their customers, the shops have consolidating their operation and have relocated to a single 'superstore' in Salamander Court, leaving these two properties available for lease or sale.

29-31 Colbee Court is located is a central area of Phillip Service Trades precinct which is home to a number of retailers and service providers. The property is situated in a court style arrangement directly adjacent to Phillip Medical and Dental Centre.

The property is a two storey building with 2 double entry doors from Colbee Court. The property also boasts rear access from Grenville Street. The rear of the property boasts on site car parking for approx 12 cars (one being under a single car port). The building has been divided into 2 units on the ground floor and 4 units on the upper floor with a central passageway / stairwell to upper level with swing door access from Colbee Court and separate entrances to each unit, thus lending itself to Unit Titling.

The ground floor units are mostly open plan with service counters, small internal offices, service workshops and both male and female toilets plus a kitchenette. The upper level comprises 4 units off a central foyer at top of stairs, each comprising service counters. There is also one male and one female toilet plus a kitchenette at the rear of the first floor. The property also comprises secure storage enclosures to the rear of the building and security bars on all windows.

Call CBRE for more information.

Better Music is a wholly Australian owned music store successfully operating from two locations; 29-31 Colbee Court and 38 Botany Street, Phillip ACT. To better service their customers, the shops are consolidating their operation and relocating into a single 'superstore' in Salamander Court, leaving these two properties available for lease or sale.

38 Botany Street is a very well exposed property approx 100m from Hindmarsh Drive. The property is located adjacent to Phillip Market Place housing tenants such as Pizza Hut, Ali Baba, KFC, Independent Property Group, FSW Shoes, Subway, Wok it Up, Dan Murphy's and Salvos. Other neighbouring occupiers include TLC Cycles, Repco, Saddle World and Auto Pro.

The building is a single level Unit Titled development of 6 units with the subject property comprising Units 4, 5 and 6, the entire left hand side which have been opened up to form one single unit. There is a walk through arcade separating the unit from the other 3 units within the development which are occupied by TLC Cycles and the ACT Branch of the Australian Nursing Federation (ANF).

All 3 units each have separate ducted air conditioning, security bars on windows and share common toilets. The premises also have the added benefit of being north facing, thus having plenty of natural light coming through the wide shop front of approx 17m. The property also has excellent signage opportunities. The premises benefit from a rear car park (accessed via double doors) with a total of 10 designated spaces for Units 4, 5 & 6 on the Units Plan. The premises can be accessed via the shop front on Botany Street, the rear entrance from Grenville Court or the additional 2 entrances from the central arcade. It can therefore easily be split back to 3 separate units, giving the flexibility to sell / lease them individually.

Phillip Market Place is an established commercial precinct completed in 2001, located in a prominent position on the western intersection of Botany Street and Hindmarsh Drive. The development is a U-shape design, with plenty of parking in the centre and vehicular access from both Botany Street and Hindmarsh Drive.

The demand to occupy premises in Phillip Market Place is high and the development is currently fully occupied with a great tenant mix including KFC, Subway, Pizza Hut, Ali Baba, Dan Murphy, FSW Shoe Warehouse, The Salvation Army and Onya Bike Warehouse.

The unit is one of 9 in the development, situated on the western side of the development, adjacent to the entrance driveway and with good exposure from Botany Street.

The unit provides a modern freestanding single level commercial/retail unit providing 198sqm of commercial accommodation comprising a reception area, two meeting rooms, 4 offices, two open plan office areas, document preparation area, kitchenette and amenities.

The building has ducted air conditioning, security system with cameras, front awning and full height aluminium framed glazed shop front windows.

The unit is currently leased to Canberra's leading residential real estate agency, Independent Property Group expiring 22 Feb 2014!

Call Mark Nicholls of CB Richard Ellis for further information!
